description.narrative: Health, nutrition and WASH policies continued to be strengthened in 2021 with technical support from UNICEF, resulting in: 100 per cent of health facilities at national and sub-national level implementing early essential newborn care in 2021; a potential legal solution for sustainable funding mechanisms to treat the annual burden of 200,000 children under 5 years with severe acute malnutrition (SAM); and ensuring targets to address equity gaps for water and sanitation services under the national target programmes. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2022
